<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406640>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Phragmatopoma californica (Fewkes, 1889). A, Complete body, dorsal view. B, Opercular crown, top view. C, Operculum, lateral view. D, Median ridge. E, Outer paleae. F–G, Middle paleae; G, Rough margin. H, Inner paleae. I, Parathoracic lanceolate notochaetae. J, Parathoracic lanceolate neurochaetae. K, Abdominal uncini. L, Verticillate abdominal chaetae. Scale bars: A: 2 mm; B, D: 500μm; C: 1 mm; E, G–H: 100 μm; F, I: 200 μm; J: 20 μm; K–L: 10 μm. Abbreviation: pc, peduncle caudal; mp, middle paleae; op, outer paleae; mr, median ridge; pl, median plume." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4406640/files/figure.png" .

